42  Under the program  Army enlisted men were sent to various colleges and universities to take coursework in engineering and allied subjects  The first ASTP students arrived at VMI on May 7  1943  the program ended on April 27  1946  with a total of 2  148 having taken part in the Institute s ASTP courses  These  Army students  were typically stationed at VMI for a few weeks or months and then were sent overseas or for additional training elswhere  They were not enrolled as VMI cadets and are not carried on the rolls as VMI alumni  However  shortly after the war Institute officials compiled a complete roster of the men who trained at VMI  which is available below  View selected documents from the VMI Archives ASTP Roster   Course Description  A list of all men who trained at VMI  May 1943 April 1946 VMI Yearbook  ASTP Section  1944  Excerpt   Cadet Life during World War II From an essay by James M  Morgan  Jr Archives   Records   World War II   Army Specialized Training Program at VMI Archives   Records   World War II   Army Specialized Training Program at VMI Archives Records     VMI During World War II Army Specialized Training Program  ASTP  Overview   Selected Documents  World War II top level  The Army Specialized Training Program  ASTP  was established by the War Department in 1942  Under the program  Army enlisted men were sent to various colleges and universities to take coursework in engineering and allied subjects  The first ASTP students arrived at VMI on May 7  1943  the program ended on April 27  1946  with a total of 2  148 having taken part in the Institute s ASTP courses  These  Army students  were typically stationed at VMI for a few weeks or months and then were sent overseas or for additional training elswhere  They were not enrolled as VMI cadets and are not carried on the rolls as VMI alumni  However  shortly after the war Institute officials compiled a complete roster of the men who trained at VMI  which is available below  View selected docum